for a very active guild. Thanks for your time. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueckol.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eckol</A> at: 8/23/02 12:15:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugustymindstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gusty Mindstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/23/02 4:56:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=345.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Considering changing servers</span><hr size=1> Karana is one of the oldest servers and has a high population.(Back when you could see the number of people on line, Karana was 1-3rd on number of people on line.)  Has a high european population (French, Danes and also a couple of Asian Guilds).  Karana is a rotation server meaning that these mobs have a waiting list on what guild can kill. The waiting list is very much enforced by all, including the Uber guilds. <br><br>Some of the mobs on rotation<br><br>Vox<br>Naggy<br>Vennril Sathir<br>Plane of Air<br>Plane of Fear<br>Plane of Hate<br>all Kunark Dragons except Ragefire (includes Trak)<br>North ToV<br><br>and a few more not sure off the top of my head (some of the west wing named dragons in ToV)<br><br>Currently an agreement by the uber guilds not to wake the sleeper.  The uber guild will always leave the first warder up.  Which may or may not change when the new ST changes go in effect, I haven't heard anything on it.<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulagdalentarcho.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lagdalen Tarcho</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Companion</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/23/02 5:57:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=345.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.engtong.com/Valoran/images/60x60/lagdalen60x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Considering changing servers</span><hr size=1> You mentioned looking at larger guilds. In that respect you need to look at wether you're interested in mandatory attendance, casual but large raids, possibly an alliance... there are many variables <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Probably one of your more important choices being - what language of guild you want to choose. English, French, Japanese, German, Mix.. we got em all hehe.<br><br>Here's some examples of some of the larger guilds and alliances on the larger rotations. (that I can think of off the top of my head so forgive me if I missed you, it wasn't intentional)<br><br>english guilds<br><br>- Valoran<br>- Nightbane<br>- Grey Hawke<br>- The Silent Watch<br>- Farsight<br>- Diamond's Edge<br><br>for other languages..<br><br>- Fama Volat (Japanese)<br>- Novae (French)<br>- Lance Dragon (French)<br>- Aargh (French)<br>- Drachenreiter (German)<br><br>For alliances...<br><br>- Ashborne Alliance<br>- AoVB Alliance<br><br>aaaaaand I have run out of names heh. I'd say your best bet is to start a lvl 1, come on and do a few /w searches for lvl 60's and then see which guild seems to have alot of people and then ask around for guild web sites.<br><br>Karana is an awesome server and people that enjoy the game but dont want the forced stress of competing for spawns, love it here. As fair warning - We need a server split, just cause we're just that old and have that many people, but overall it's a good place to be. Those that like it here usually like it alot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>If you wanna post up anything more specific you're looking for I'm sure people here can send you links or more info, good luck with your choice! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center> <img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/flarren/LagKommipic.gif> </center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/upalankakarana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PalankaKarana</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.tripod.co.uk/redhotant/icons/iconoc01.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(8/24/02 2:23:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=345.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Considering changing servers</span><hr size=1> Karana is a rather fluffy server compared to others.  Don't be surprised if it's not as advanced as other servers.<br><br>Lendinara the Keeper and Yelinak are on rotation too.<br><br> <p>-- --<BR><b><i>The Right Reverend Palanka, Th.D.</i></b><BR>High Priest of Truth, Karana Server.  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=119628">Magelo Profile</a><BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/upalankakarana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PalankaKarana</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.tripod.co.uk/redhotant/icons/iconoc01.gif" BORDER=0> at: 8/24/02 2:25:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzizzerzazzerzuz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zizzerzazzerzuz</A></span><br> <span class=